{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"changeUser"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"userId","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"sdkAuthSignature"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"text":"fileID","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s12StaticStringV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"StaticString"},{"kind":"text","text":" = "},{"text":"#fileID","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"line","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UInt","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Su"},{"text":" = ","kind":"text"},{"text":"#line","kind":"keyword"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["iOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"userId","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The new user identifier.","type":"text"}]}]},{"name":"sdkAuthSignature","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The optional user SDK authentication signature.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When a user first uses Braze on a device, they are considered “anonymous”. Use this method to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"identify a user with a unique ID, which enables the following:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the same user is identified on another device, their user profile, usage history and event history"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be shared across devices."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If your app is used on the same device by multiple people, you can assign each of them a unique","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"identifier to track them separately. Only the most recent user on a particular device will receive"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"push notifications and in-app messages."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When you request a user switch (which is any call to ","type":"text"},{"code":"changeUser","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" where the new user ID is not the same"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as the existing user ID), the current session for the previous user (anonymous or not) is automatically","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ended and a new session is started. Similarly, following a call to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"changeUser"},{"type":"text","text":", any events which fire are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"guaranteed to be for the new user. If an in-flight server request completes for the old user after the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"user switch, no events will fire, so you do not need to worry about filtering out events from Braze for old users.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Additionally, if you identify a user which has never been identified on another device, the entire history of that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"user as an “anonymous” user on this device will be preserved and associated with the newly identified user."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"However, if you identify a user which has been identified in another device, any history which was already","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"flushed to the server for the anonymous user on this device will be merged into the identified user.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(See: ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.braze.com\/docs\/api\/endpoints\/user_data\/post_users_merge#merge_updates-behavior","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":")"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note: Once you identify a user, you cannot revert to the “anonymous” user. The transition from anonymous"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to identified tracking is only allowed ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"once"}]},{"type":"text","text":" because the initial anonymous user receives special treatment to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"allow for preservation of their history. As a result, we recommend against changing the user ID just because"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"your app has entered a “logged out” state because it makes you unable to target the previously logged out","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"user with re-engagement campaigns. If you anticipate multiple users on the same device, but only want to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"target one of them when your app is in a logged out state, we recommend separately keeping track of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"user ID you want to target while logged out and switching back to that user ID as part of your app’s logout process.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that the current user’s information and ID can be retrieved at any time via the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/user-swift.property","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" module."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/brazekit\/braze\/changeuser(userid:sdkauthsignature:fileid:line:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"BrazeKit"}],"symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","title":"changeUser(userId:sdkAuthSignature:fileID:line:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"changeUser","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"userId"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"sdkAuthSignature","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"fileID"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"StaticString","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s12StaticStringV"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"line","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Su","text":"UInt","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"extendedModule":"BrazeKit","externalID":"s:8BrazeKit0A0C10changeUser6userId16sdkAuthSignature6fileID4lineySS_SSSgs12StaticStringVSutF"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit","doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Change the current identified Braze user.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/changeUser(userId:sdkAuthSignature:fileID:line:)"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/User-swift.class","doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/user-swift.property"],"title":"User","anchor":"User"}],"references":{"doc://Braze/documentation/BrazeKit/Braze":{"url":"\/documentation\/brazekit\/braze","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze","title":"Braze","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Braze","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is the main entry point of the BrazeKit module and provides access to all its features."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Braze","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://Braze/documentation/BrazeKit":{"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/brazekit","type":"topic","title":"BrazeKit","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The main Braze framework providing user sessions, attributes and events logging, push notification support."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit"},"doc://Braze/documentation/BrazeKit/Braze/User-swift.class":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"User","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/brazekit\/braze\/user-swift.class","type":"topic","title":"Braze.User","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The user module allows setting attributes on the current user."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"User"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/User-swift.class"},"doc://Braze/documentation/BrazeKit/Braze/user-swift.property":{"url":"\/documentation\/brazekit\/braze\/user-swift.property","title":"user","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/user-swift.property","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"user"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"User","preciseIdentifier":"s:8BrazeKit0A0C4UserC"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"User module."}]},"https://www.braze.com/docs/api/endpoints/user_data/post_users_merge#merge_updates-behavior":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":"List of merge fields","type":"text"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/www.braze.com\/docs\/api\/endpoints\/user_data\/post_users_merge#merge_updates-behavior","title":"List of merge fields","url":"https:\/\/www.braze.com\/docs\/api\/endpoints\/user_data\/post_users_merge#merge_updates-behavior"},"doc://Braze/documentation/BrazeKit/Braze/changeUser(userId:sdkAuthSignature:fileID:line:)":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/changeUser(userId:sdkAuthSignature:fileID:line:)","title":"changeUser(userId:sdkAuthSignature:fileID:line:)","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/brazekit\/braze\/changeuser(userid:sdkauthsignature:fileid:line:)","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Change the current identified Braze user.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"changeUser"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"userId","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"sdkAuthSignature","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fileID","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s12StaticStringV","text":"StaticString"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"line"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UInt","preciseIdentifier":"s:Su"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}]}}}